featured_reviews.review_id:
Safa Masjid is a hidden gem nestled in the heart of the city. This historical mosque is a testament to the rich heritage of our country and a peaceful oasis for anyone seeking solace amidst the hustle and bustle of daily life.

The first thing that strikes you upon arrival is the impeccable maintenance of the premises. The beautifully landscaped gardens are a sight to behold. The well-kept pathways and the surrounding greenery add to the overall charm of the place. Safa Masjid is a serene haven, inviting visitors to take a leisurely stroll or simply sit and absorb the tranquil atmosphere.

The mosque itself is a marvel of architecture. Its intricate design and historical significance make it a must-visit for history enthusiasts and architecture aficionados. The interior of the mosque is equally impressive, with its exquisite detailing and a sense of spirituality that envelops you as you enter.

However, there is one minor issue that caught my attention during my visit--the pond near the mosque was filled with algae. While this did not significantly detract from the overall experience, it was a small blemish on an otherwise pristine environment. It would be wonderful if the authorities could address this concern and restore the pond to its natural beauty.

In conclusion, Safa Masjid is a place of historical, architectural, and spiritual importance that offers a peaceful respite from the chaos of the outside world. Its well-maintained surroundings and the sense of tranquility it provides make it a worthy destination. I would highly recommend a visit, with the hope that the issue with the pond can be resolved to further enhance this delightful place.

featured_reviews.review_id:
recently visited Safa Masjid in Goa and I was thoroughly impressed with the beauty and serenity of this historic mosque. The architecture is stunning, with intricate carvings and a beautiful dome that is a sight to behold. The peaceful atmosphere inside the mosque was a welcome respite from the hustle and bustle of Goa's busy streets.

The staff at Safa Masjid were incredibly friendly and welcoming, and I felt at ease exploring the mosque and learning more about its history. It was fascinating to hear about the important role that the mosque has played in the local community over the years.

Overall, I would highly recommend a visit to Safa Masjid for anyone visiting Goa. Whether you are interested in history, architecture, or simply looking for a peaceful place to reflect and pray, this mosque is a must-see.

The mosque situated centre of the pond and peripheral garden. So the environment is very soothing and Sufi.
The only one mosque like this architecture in India I ever seen.

Safa Mosque or Safa Shahouri Mosque is a mosque located at Ponda within Goa, India. It is a sixteenth century Islamic Monument. The mosque has a complex consisting of garden and fountains. The terracotta tile roof accommodates a rectangular prayer hall.

It is an ASI protected Monument of National Importance in Goa.
